article.headline: Georgia St 86, Lipscomb 62
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Kevin Thomas scored 20 points and Boyd Copeland added 18 to lead Georgia State to an 86-62 Atlantic Sun Conference victory over Lipscomb on Sunday. Thomas hit six of nine shots from 3-point range and the Panthers (12-12, 9-7) hit 13 of 19 as a team. Eddie Ard scored 16 points and James Poindexter 15 for Lipscomb (12-11, 7-9), which hit a trio of 3-pointers to take an early 17-8 lead before the Panthers took control of the game with runs of 11-0 and 17-2. Georgia State built a 42-27 halftime lead on the way to their seventh victory in 10 games. Sylvester Morgan set a Georgia State season record for blocked shots with his 63rd and 64th. Marcus Brown added 15 points for the Panthers and Herman Favors had 12. Shaun Durant added 10 ponts for Lipscomb.
